doc.after: Douglas Thomas Ring was an Australian cricketer who played for Victoria and Australia in 13 Tests from 1948 to 1953 In 129 first class cricket matches he took 426 wickets bowling leg spin and he had a top score of 145 runs which was the only century of his career
